For every Result r and every Presenter method X, stripANSI(ColorPresenter.X(r)) MUST equal PlainPresenter.X(r) byte-for-byte. This is the correctness invariant that makes Color safe to implement independently of Plain. It is enforced by a battery test in cli/output/color_test.go covering: synced, drifted marker, drifted spec, both-changed, deleted spec, deleted marker, no-baseline, multi-edge expanded, --all with multiple edges, empty state, unlinked warning, and every Ok/Error/Text/Version shape. See <ref spec="output_impl.guardrail_test">guardrail test</ref>.